done-so-far: Both layers of the content-toolkit Swift gap landed and verified. Layer 1 (3b8f67da3): content-module data plumbing — SwiftV2Commands makes a second non-fatal RunNativeV2.compile call per emit, extracts NativeContentModule data via the existing self-hosted-tower ABI (specs/v2.1-native-content.md, unmodified), encodes via the existing NativeContentCodec, embeds as a base64 Swift string literal (Sources/AppCore/ContentModules.swift, always generated). SwiftRuntime.scala ports ContentNativePlugin.scala's 13 data accessors (contentDocument/contentSection/contentBlock/contentData/contentMetadata/contentPlainText/contentToMarkdown/contentModules/contentModule/contentModuleSection/contentModuleBlock/contentModuleData/contentModuleMetadata) plus a from-scratch Swift binary decoder for the documented NativeContentCodec format. Found+fixed a real Xcode-project-generation gap (SwiftXcodeProject.sourcePaths didn't include the new file — swiftc -typecheck alone didn't catch it, only a real xcodebuild did). Layer 2 (e93a879de): contentToolkitNode/Block/Section rendering — faithful port of ContentToolkitJs.scala for static Markdown (headings/paragraphs/lists/tables) + multi-doc id lookup + safe-block wrapper; interactive controls (toolkit: links, @ui=toolkit YAML, components/actions/row-bindings/slots) explicitly out of scope with a clear runtime diagnostic. Found+fixed a real nested-list bug (BulletList/OrderedList items are List[List[ContentBlock]], caught by a real xcodebuild, not typecheck). Verified against busi's actual production content: offlineGuideToolkit() and offlineGuideChecklist() (real offline_guide.ssc) both build through a real xcodebuild and run without crashing. Full v2SwiftBackend suite 54/54 green (two pre-existing file-list assertions updated for the new always-present ContentModules.swift).
next: post comprehensive summary to scalascript rozum room for review (matching the __try__/JSON precedent — foundational Swift-backend work gets a review pass before considered fully done). Awaiting room feedback; will push branch + release claim once reviewed, or address findings first if any surface.
